OL,7,F"I thought it might have been the
OL,8,F'baby blues' because that's what you
OL,9,Fhear a lot of people talking about
OL,10,Fafter birth," said Ross, "but then one
OL,11,Fmorning she woke up and said to me,
OL,12,F'You guys would be better off if I
OL,13,Fwasn't here' and that was an immediate
OL,14,Fred flag and when I knew I needed to
OL,15,Fget some help."
OL,17,FRoss immediately contacted the
OL,18,Fcouple's health visitor who spoke
OL,19,Fdirectly with Gemma and referred her
OL,20,Fto a perinatal mental health
OL,21,Fconsultant.
